channel.title: Rt3cpp - 317 concept server written in C++
channel.description:
[size=14pt][b]Disclaimers:[/b][/size] This is a public project of mine, anyone who is interested may fork it at any time. Keep in mind, this is a concept server; meaning, if you're looking for completeness or extremely polished code you've come to the wrong place.
[size=14pt][b]Any Dependencies?[/b][/size]
[ul][li]standard c++ libraries[/li] [li]certain boost libraries (the README will usually say which ones)[/li] [li]A c++ compiler (I suggest g++)[/li][/ul]
[size=14pt][b]What's done?[/b][/size] Just about nothing at the moment other than a working translation of the well known cryption and stream classes (now known as ISAACCipher and ByteStream/PacketFactory) and a minimal server skeleton. I've just started this today.
[size=14pt][b]When's this going to be done?[/b][/size] Do not know. This is a side project that I am offering up publicly so that on the off chance there's C/C++ programmers around these parts, they have something to work on in the open.
[size=14pt][b]I want to take a look/contribute![/b][/size] You're in luck, you can check it out/view it/fork it all via github! [code]https://github.com/dabel/RT3[/code]
Have fun/comment.
